Hi there..thanks for stopping by to view my profile. Here is a cheerful, easygoing, down to earth person whose upbringing has been in an ambiance entrenched with modernity and also embedded with traditional culture & heritage. I have a modern & cosmopolitan outlook but nevertheless I am basically a person with core Indian ethics and have strong faith in the virtues of Indian culture & family values. I believe in simplicity of thought and ways. I cherish my self-reliance, capable of taking decisions independently and I speak my mind......but I am not over-assertive & neither a hardnosed type......I consider that in any association individual views & decisions should be valued and given due respect but mutual discussion & concurrence is more essential & always appreciated. By and large I prefer to take life as it comes & like to lead a well balanced life in which there is a sound equilibrium among all the spheres. My leisure time interests are reading books, listening to music, travelling, watching movies & T.V., net surfing,......and I love to chat & hang out with friends. My hobbies include cooking (this is something I really love & enjoy doing) & painting (for this of course I hardly find time these days). People who know me well enough describe me as caring, understanding, dependable & adjustable.,"I am in search of a Soul Mate who is well-read & well-established & has presentable looks. Well, I am not on the lookout for an epitome of perfection......am just looking forward to sharing my life with someone who is honest, fun-loving, compassionate, caring, understanding and has the ability to appreciate as well as reciprocate my thoughts and feelings. I am seeking a life partner who can become my BEST FRIEND...... someone who would make me his best friend too......while at the same time both of us would also give each other our own individual space in life. A well educated and cultured person. Honest, caring, sensitive individual who stands for what she believes in. Has lived abroad for some years. I'm an incurable romantic. I will marry the day I find someone who loves me the way I always wished to be loved. I would like to find a person who is mature, caring, understanding, supportive and above all sensitive to my feelings. There should be trust and respect in a relationship too. When the time is right, the decision of life will reveal itself. I firmly believe in destiny. It's odd how you are reflected in another person, in the sense that you recognize yourself. column1: As a twenty-something, I may have heightened the anxiety level of my family members when I decided to set my personal priorities in the early '90s. My marriage certainly didn't figure at the top of the agenda at that time. I wanted to go out and explore the world. Conquer the space I would occupy in the months and years ahead. Achieve a certain degree of harmony with my surroundings. Take my decisions at a time of my own choosing. Focus on my professional skill-set. Be of use. Be confident. And be on my own. I did not do this to scoff at the support structure of the immediate family and the larger clan which was available to me at all points of time. I value it as much now as I did then. I wanted to attain a level of professional recognition and success. The present decade has brought all of these. God has been kind. Experience of different facets of life has brought maturity and perspective. The paradigm has shifted from the struggle for survival to stability and more success. Perhaps a few more years have passed in the process of this achievement. Perhaps the probability of finding a life partner at age 36 has relatively diminished. But perhaps other human beings have gone through a similar cycle. I am now ready to carve out a shared destiny through marriage. One that will bring mutual joy and happiness. One that will be based on compassion and understanding. One that will kindle love. One that will have longevity. I have had a happy childhood in Bombay with a family of migrants that came here from west Punjab in 1947. My father studied law at Bombay University and has been practicing it at the Bombay High Court for over 50 years. My mother is a housewife who, besides me, has raised my elder brother to be a textile professional. It is a different matter that my brother has passionately followed his dream & successfully switched his career to a technology-based occupation. As a US resident, he now works for a New Jersey-based company and lives in the same state with his wife and two school-going children. My sister-in-law grew up in Bombay and now works for a renowned multi-national travel house in NYC. After experimenting with my career choice initially, I have settled down as a computer software professional. I am presently employed by a Mumbai-based MNC as a Project Leader. I have fewer interests because of paucity of time but I am passionate about the ones I have. I love dancing, aerobics, health gigs, music and shopping. I love to have long conversations with friends and family. I love to travel. I have had extended stay in UK, the US, Thailand and Muscat.,"Looking for an educated, well settled, caring, honest and responsible person who does not drink or smoke. Someone who is well spoken, intelligent and sophisticated.",,34 to 42,26 May 1972,,India,Mumbai,Slim,,,,,,,Very Fair ,,Self,Other School/ Graduation,"41 yrs, 5ft 5in,

Hi, I am Meenakshi Gurung, born and bought up in Dehra Dun, Uttaranchal and now working in Delhi since 2000. 
I am simple natured and take the life as it comes. But of course a bold person always ready to solve and come out of any kind of situation. According to me, internal beauty is more important than the physical appearance.
My family members and friends say I am a caring and lovable person. I believes in the truth ---- 'Live and let others live'. I use to spend my leisure time - reading articles/books, watching good movies, listening music, cooking, helping needy peoples and of course doing prayers for all. 
I feel marriage will happen as per the God's wish. It is an alliance of life, a meeting of two souls which is possible only through the full contribution and adjustment from the both to meet and march towards one life time journey. I start searching for my soul mate at this stage of life as I suppose myself to be confident to proceed forward to build a best nest of my coming life.
Family:
From my family front we are three sisters and I am the second one. We all three are working and my eldest sister is happily married. The younger sister still wants to make advancements in her career. My father is a enjoying his retired life at our Dehra Dun home and my mother is a simple and adorable house wife.
For the life partner:
I prefer my life partner to be loving, caring, responsible, honest and believe in life long relationship and respect for each others values.,"For the life partner:

column1:
I belong to a cultured, well settled, Bengali Brahmin family. Have grown up in an industrial town in Madhya Pradesh, and thereafter moved to metro cities. One younger brother, married with kids. Parents, retired.

I am a well placed professional, and have held senior positions very early in my life. I have enjoyed challenges that high pressure jobs throw up. But, I believe that in a professional life of roughly 40 years, people should try out various options. Thus, after completing my PhD (pursuing currently), I may like to move fulltime into academics, as I enjoy teaching, and this vocation provides more time for self and family. I have Masters in mathematics, and MBA. Have done a short course in management in UK on scholarship.

I am slim, good looking, and carry myself well. I look calm and collected, and generally at peace with the world. By nature, I am a happy person. Easygoing, smiling and filled with joie de vivre describes me best. Most likely, because of my nature and happy disposition, I donot look my age.

I live in a joint family, which includes kids. Strong middle class values, traditional yet modern outlook to life, love of learning and ability to reach out to the needy keeps me grounded. I am not very goal oriented as a person, rather I enjoy the journey of life.

I love travelling, reading, music, cooking, and keeping a good & welcoming household. For my family, I continue to be the holiday planner, chief host cum cook for get-togethers, as well as navigator for weekend short travels!

I am planning to settle down with some one who is well qualified, financially well placed, belongs to a cultured family and most importantly, has a strong base of decent value system. Intelligent, jolly, ability to enjoy journey of life are the key qualities. Location is not a constraint; I can relocate easily. 

I believe that marriage is based on love and liking, but also on mutual trust, regard and respect for each other.,"I am planning to settle down with some one who is well qualified, financially well placed, belongs to a cultured family and most importantly, has a strong base of decent value system. column1:
Dancing is a perpendicular expression of a horizontal desire. It needs nothing but a cause. No good dancer can dance if he has nothing in his mind. One needs to have a desire if one needs to dance perfectly.
I have always admired the idea of knowing how to dance. That is what motivated me to learn dancing. I got trained for some time and now I can dance without any hitch. Before that, I thought dancing needs to have a lot of dimensions and rules, but after learning it I realized how free and stress-free dancing is. It does not need any fix steps or forms. All it needs is desire to do it.

My family is very close and very well bonded. I get a feeling of belongingness when I am around them. They make me feel I am worthy of a lot of love. 
Apart from that, I love decorating my house and enjoy it immensely. Whenever I am free at home, I start decorating my room. I have helped many friends of mine in decorating their houses.
